üéØ Purpose

The Video Contest module in Flixbit is designed to:
	‚Ä¢	Engage users and sellers through interactive video-based competitions.
	‚Ä¢	Promote sellers‚Äô brands, influencer campaigns, or sponsored content.
	‚Ä¢	Reward users for watching, rating, or participating in video-based contests.

This feature transforms advertising into gamified engagement, where users earn rewards (Flixbit points) by interacting with videos ‚Äî not just viewing them.

‚∏ª

‚öôÔ∏è How the Video Contest Works (End-to-End Flow)

‚∏ª

1. Video Upload / Contest Creation

Who can create:
	‚Ä¢	Sub-Admins ‚Äì to promote regional or sponsored contests.
	‚Ä¢	Sellers ‚Äì to advertise their products or influencer videos (requires approval).

When creating a video contest, the uploader specifies:
	‚Ä¢	üé¨ Video Source: Uploaded file or external link (e.g., YouTube, TikTok).
	‚Ä¢	üè∑Ô∏è Contest Title and Description
	‚Ä¢	üìÖ Start & End Date (defines contest duration)
	‚Ä¢	üèÜ Reward Type: Points, vouchers, or coupons for top-rated participants or viewers.
	‚Ä¢	üß© Category/Tag: (e.g., Food, Fitness, Entertainment).
	‚Ä¢	‚öôÔ∏è Region/Target Audience: Specific city or user group.
	‚Ä¢	üí∞ Sponsorship/Ad Budget: (for sellers if it‚Äôs a paid promo).

Once created, the video contest is submitted for admin approval before it appears in the app.

‚∏ª

2. Admin/Sub-Admin Approval

Before being published, each video contest goes through:
	‚Ä¢	Content Verification: To ensure it meets policy guidelines.
	‚Ä¢	Relevance Check: Based on target audience and category.
	‚Ä¢	Reward Validation: Confirm rewards and points are legitimate.

After approval, it becomes visible to users in their regional or interest-based feed.

‚∏ª

3. User Participation

Users can access video contests in several ways:
	‚Ä¢	From the Home Screen video carousel (auto-playing top videos).
	‚Ä¢	From the Video Contest section/tab.
	‚Ä¢	Through Push Notifications promoting new contests.

Users can:
	‚Ä¢	Watch the video directly inside the app.
	‚Ä¢	Like üëç or dislike üëé it (or give a star rating).
	‚Ä¢	Comment (optional, if enabled).
	‚Ä¢	Vote for their favorite entry.
	‚Ä¢	Share it on social media (Snapchat, Instagram, Facebook).

Each action can be rewarded with Flixbit points, encouraging participation.

‚∏ª

4. Contest Rules and Timing

Each contest has:
	‚Ä¢	Start time and end time ‚Äì displayed clearly to all participants.
	‚Ä¢	Voting Window ‚Äì users can only rate during the active period.
	‚Ä¢	Winner Announcement ‚Äì handled automatically or by Admin after the contest ends.

Once the timer ends:
	‚Ä¢	The system calculates votes/ratings.
	‚Ä¢	The top-rated videos or creators are marked as winners.
	‚Ä¢	Winners receive in-app notifications and Flixbit rewards.

‚∏ª

5. Reward Distribution

Rewards depend on contest type:
	‚Ä¢	Viewer Rewards:
	‚Ä¢	Users who watched or rated videos earn small Flixbit points (to keep engagement high).
	‚Ä¢	Creator/Seller Rewards:
	‚Ä¢	Influencers or sellers whose videos receive top ratings win higher-value rewards (points, promo credits, or coupons).

Rewards appear directly in:
	‚Ä¢	User‚Äôs Wallet (Flixbit balance)
	‚Ä¢	In-App Notification Feed

‚∏ª

6. Video Contest Integration with Other Modules
Module              -   How It Connects
Flixbit Wallet      -   Viewers and creators earn or spend points through participation.
Push Notifications  -   Used to announce new contests, winners, and trending videos.
Reward System       -   Winners receive redeemable rewards or coupons.
Offers System       -   Some contests promote specific seller offers.
Review System       -   After contest ends, users can rate seller/influencer accounts.
Analytics Dashboard -   Admin/Sub-Admin track engagement, votes, and reach metrics.

7. Seller and Influencer Benefits

The video contest gives sellers and influencers multiple marketing advantages:
	‚Ä¢	Brand Exposure: Videos reach targeted demographics through push notifications.
	‚Ä¢	Follower Growth: Viewers who interact automatically become followers.
	‚Ä¢	Performance Insights: Analytics on views, ratings, and audience engagement.
	‚Ä¢	Reward Monetization: Sellers can offer in-app coupons or discounts as part of their contest campaigns.

Example:

A restaurant seller runs a ‚ÄúBest Dish Video Contest.‚Äù
Users vote on influencer-made videos.
Top 3 videos win vouchers or free meals.
Voters earn Flixbit points for participation.

‚∏ª

8. Admin & Sub-Admin Control
Role         - Capabilities
Admin        - Approve video contests, manage global content, control reward values, monitor activity and analytics.
Sub-Admin    - Manage contests within assigned regions, moderate comments and engagement, track user participation.

Both can:
	‚Ä¢	Delete or flag inappropriate videos.
	‚Ä¢	Adjust contest timelines.
	‚Ä¢	Issue bonus rewards or promotional boosts.

‚∏ª

9. Analytics & Tracking

The system tracks:
	‚Ä¢	Number of views, likes/dislikes, and shares.
	‚Ä¢	Average watch duration.
	‚Ä¢	Conversion of viewers to followers.
	‚Ä¢	Total points earned and distributed.

Sellers can view performance for their own videos, while Admin/Sub-Admin see platform-wide analytics.

‚∏ª

10. Example Flow

Example Contest:
	1.	A fitness influencer uploads a ‚ÄúPush-Up Challenge‚Äù video contest.
	2.	Admin approves it and sets reward rules.
	3.	Users in that region receive a notification.
	4.	They watch the video, vote, and share it.
	5.	Contest ends ‚Üí system ranks top-rated videos.
	6.	Winners are rewarded automatically.
	7.	Notifications sent to all participants.

‚∏ª

11. Monetization Angle
	‚Ä¢	Sellers can pay (via Flixbit or direct payment) to feature their video contest.
	‚Ä¢	Paid contests get better placement in user feeds.
	‚Ä¢	Ads tied to video contests boost Flixbit economy by encouraging point purchases.

‚∏ª

12. User Experience

When a user opens the app:
	‚Ä¢	The top portion of the dashboard auto-plays trending or active video contests.
	‚Ä¢	Below are quick-access icons for:
